      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "fries",
      "amount": "1 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "peanut oil",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a grill to medium high heat.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together coconut milk, red wine, soy sauce, brown sugar, coriander, and cumin.",
    "Add the chicken to the bowl and marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Thread the marinated chicken onto skewers.",
    "Grill the chicken for 5-7 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, heat the peanut oil in a large pot to 350 degrees.",
    "Fry the fries in the peanut oil until crispy and golden brown.",
    "Serve the grilled chicken on a talavera plate with the fried fries and your choice of dipping sauce."
  ],
